reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. These are wonderful!!! Much shorter than I had imagined but that’s okay! They’re super sturdy and I was able to put 2 of them together in under an hour. Instructions were very clear and these even came with the tools needed! (Small screwdriver & Allen wrench) super happy about this purchase!The drawers are not super smooth at the beginning but after opening a couple times it smooths out perfectly

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cute nightstand but annoying to put together.
reviews.reviewText: This is a really nice nightstand but it took a good hour to put together and there were a bunch of steps. For a nightstand that small and at that price point, I did not expect to have to put together so much of it.If you have not started putting it together yet, please note that you should have a cloth or papertowels around to wipe your hands with because one step involves separating the track mechanism, which is coated in lubricant to keep the tracks running smoothly. There is no way to do this without getting the grease/lubricant on your hands and it's a pain in the butt to remove.That said, despite the million steps of putting it together, it looks nice and is sturdy, of good quality, and fits the aesthetic of my bedroom. I have a small bedroom but a kingsized bed so a small nightstand is essential and having one that has a powerstrip in it is really nice.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Charging Up in Style!
reviews.reviewText: My bedroom just got a stylish upgrade with the Aobafuir Rattan Nightstand. The 2-drawer setup? Perfect for my bedtime essentials. And that black with gold frame? Mid-century modern vibes that are straight-up Instagram-worthy. But here's the real kicker - the built-in charging station. No more hunting for outlets; it's like my devices have a designated charging spot. Stylish and functional? This nightstand is a total win!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Use a drill for assembly.
reviews.reviewText: This is not the first time I have assembled furniture, but I would highly suggest that you use a drill even though the instructions state not too. I struggled to understand the instructions regarding the drawer mechanism and looked for a video. There were some QR codes on the instructions but that led me nowhere. So I searched youtube and found a couple videos. They weren't my exact piece but enough to show what I couldn't understand. Both videos showed the guys using drill. Man I wish I would have. By the time I finished my hand had blisters and was sore. I was not able to complete the assembly in 60 minutes.There were some good points. The hardward and pieces were pretty good quality. As well as these were shipped there was a marred corner, but I was able to hide. Also, while I was screwing in the A screws my hand slipped and broke the board, but I tried again, and it did manage to screw in securely.In prepping for assembly I did count all the hardware and checked the pieces. I thought there was the correct amout of E screws but the last stem I was short 1. Luckily there is a small bag of spare parts, I should give a star just for that.Finally complete. Yes it looks like the product description. It will work for what the intended purchase was. A bedside table, although I will need to be careful, so I don't tip it over. Those high spindle straight legs aren't wobbly but don't give much stability to it either. I might take some double stick tape and stick it to the wall.I'm not sure that it's worth the price? It's not a rip off but try to get it when there is a discount.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Overall pretty nice, but a pain to assemble and probably not built to last
reviews.reviewText: This is in the ballpark of something you would get at a Swedish assemble-yourself furniture place. You know the one. So it's fine quality, in that arena. You won't be passing this down to your grandkids, but it'll serve its purpose as a bedside nightstand perfectly adequately. It's a little smaller than I pictured, and the assembly was a little painful. Probable took me about an hour to assemble while I watched some TV. Overall I'm happy with this purchase, but it won't exactly knock anybody's socks off, either. Solid 4 stars.

reviews.reviewText: I’d love to leave a better review but the package arrived with no assembly instructions and I’ve been unable to find any online

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Small, well designed
reviews.reviewText: This nightstand is a nice little table. It’s made of MDF, and assembles like similar furniture. The instructions are well written and the kit is well designed, and includes the necessary tools (Philips screw driver and hex/allen wrench).Assembly does take some time, it’s not a 15minute project, but once complete it is solid and looks good.The drawers are tall enough for a tissue box, and even fit a resmed airsense cpap machine.It’s lightweight, so is easily moved, but that does mean that it’s also easily bumped, which may topple things on top. The drawers have a little resistance at the end to keep them in, but it require enough force to push the table a bit as well. I expect that to wear in and not be a problem long term, but it’s simply a lightweight piece of furniture.The wood appears coated with plastic, so it may survive water without the bubbling typical of this type of furniture.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I should have looked more closely at the dimensions, but I was paying more attention to the product photos showing this nightstand being as tall or taller than an adult-sized bed. In reality, our bed which is a pretty typical height is significantly taller than this table. It is also tiny in all dimensions making it ideal for a child. We may try to relocate this by something like an Eames chair that is already low. The build quality is pretty good, and the instructions are pretty easy to follow once I figured out the orientation of the panels. The finish is a sparkly white with gold and tax accents. The power bank is a handy addition. This is a good table, and if it was a little larger it could be great.
